  "dqc_rules": [],
  "notes": "NCD Behavioral Risk Factors, Senior Citizens 60+ (ncd_ra_nir.xlsx 'b' sheets). Split config; Adults ('a' sheets) is a separate config (ncd_ra_adults). Province/HUC rollup (5 rows; region skipped). 2 meta cols; location NAME col 1. All risk-factor percentages divide by the Risk-Assessed count (col 2); BTI% divides by All-Smokers Total (clinically correct — BTI is offered to smokers, not the whole cohort). Smoker-All is the union of the three smoker types (tobacco+vape+both), summed per sex from the raw columns. KNOWN DATA ISSUE (RF-1, flag to DOH, not fixed here): the source header states this Risk-Assessed total 'must equal Risk Assessed in the ncd_meds template', but in the sample data An automated cross-template DQC (compare against NCD_MEDS_ADULT_RISKASSESSED) needs the D4 reconciliation rule type and is deferred. The source's single over-100% DQC is dead (off-by-one anchor, NCD Flag X-1). Annual sheet is a pure rollup, not ingested."
